prompt: If TPP(x,y) and DC(y,z) then what are the possible relationships between x and z?
answer:
If x is a tangential proper part of y (TPP(x,y)), then all points of x are contained in y (i.e., x ⊆ y). Since y and z are disconnected (DC(y,z)), they share no points at all—no interior and no boundary points. Because x ⊆ y, x cannot share any points with z either, so x and z must be disconnected (DC(x,z)). No other relation is consistent with these conditions.

### Answer:
DC(x,z)
